<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Newly Appointed Head  of Congolese Armed Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The newly appointed head of
the Congolese Armed Forces, Lieutenant-General Sylvestre Luecha,
died last week, Rwanda News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Luecha, 75, is said to have died nine days ago, at Njonja, in
Itombwe, 350 kilometers south of the capital of South Kivu
Province, Bukavu.
</P>
<P>
''We are told that he died nine days ago,'' the Congolese Rally
for Democracy (RCD) Information Minister said, quoting Mai Mai
fighters under Luecha who have surrendered to the rebel forces.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Luecha might have been shot during
skirmishes which took place in the hills of South Kivu, a breeding
ground for the Mai Mai militia, former Rwandan Hutu extremist
forces, defeated former Rwandan government soldiers (ex-FAR) and
Burundi Hutu rebels.
</P>
<P>
The RCD rebels challenged President Laurent-Desire Kabila to
show the newly appointed Chief of Armed Forces on television to
prove he was not dead.
</P>
<P>
Luecha and another Mai Mai Commander General Sikatende were
promoted last Friday, much to the dismay of Congolese rebels who
say they should rather be arrested like any members of the
renegade forces who must be netted as stipulated by Lusaka
agreement.
</P>
<P>
The rebels had threatened to resume war if Kabila did not
revise his appointments.  
</P>
</TEXT>
