<HEADLINE> Over Half of Rwandan Population Illiterate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Over 51.8 percent of the
Rwandan population is illiterate, the latest statistics given by
Rwanda show.
</P>
<P>
Rwandan Minister for Social Affairs, Charles Ntakirutinka,
highlighted the government's commitment to combating illiteracy
through the creation of more learning institutions when the Word
Literacy Day falls on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
" We all know that ignorance is the source of poverty,
infection diseases, crimes and segregation," he said, stressing
that "fighting ignorance is the first step to development,
inventiveness and eradication of divisions among the people".
</P>
</TEXT>
