<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecuador's New Finance Minister Assumes Position </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's new Finance Minister
Alfredo Arizaga Wednesday took possession of the position.
</P>
<P>
Arizaga is the third person to hold the position in just under
13 months of President Jamil Mahaud's government.
</P>
<P>
Alfredo Arizaga, 38, has consultancy experience at both
national and international levels, as he was part of the team of
experts, which worked between 1988 and 1991 on the proposal of
renegotiating the country's external debt.
</P>
<P>
The new finance minister also held the position of
vice-president in the bank La Previsora.
</P>
<P>
Among the responsibilities that the new minister will undertake
are the persuasion of the congress to accept the state budget for
the year 2000, a new tax reform, and also negotiations over the
payment of foreign debt.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador's economy is expected to contract by 7 percent this
year, said reports. The government is seeking to reduce a budget
deficit to 2.5 percent of the gross domestic product in 2000 from
4 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
