<HEADLINE> Saudi Crown Prince Holds Talks with Omani Sultan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Crown Prince Abdullah Ibn
Abdul-Aziz held talks with visiting Omani Sultan Qaboos Bin Said
Wednesday on ways of boosting bilateral cooperation to serve the
common interest of both states.
</P>
<P>
During their talks in Saudi Red Sea port city of Jiddah, the
two leaders also discussed the latest developments in the Middle
East peace process, voicing support for the latest
Palestinian-Israeli peace accord, or the Sharm el Sheikh
memorandum, the Saudi News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian-Israeli revised agreement for the Wye Accord
signed in Egyptian Red Sea resort of Sharm El-Sheikh Sunday
provides for Israeli troops pullout from another 11 percent of the
West Bank by January 20 next year, release of 350 Palestinian
political prisoners by October 8 and the start of the long-overdue
final status talks on September 13.
</P>
<P>
Omani Sultan and his entourage arrived in Jiddah on Tuesday on
a three-day official visit to the Gulf kingdom. 
</P>
