<HEADLINE> Yemeni PM Meets IMF Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni Prime Minister
Abdul-Karim al-Iryani received a visiting delegation of the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) headed by Claus Anders here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two sides reviewed the positive
developments in the economic, financial and fiscal indicators of
Yemen, including stability of the macro economic system,
improvement of the state budget, stability of the exchange
rate and decline of inflation rate to 1.00 percent.
