refugee with her family during World War II in 1942. A bilingual
leading figure in Canada's cultural life, Mme Clarkson enjoys a rich
career in broadcasting, journalism, the arts and public service, the
government sources said.
</P>
<P>
Until Wednesday's announcement, Mme Clarkson served as Chairwoman
of the Board of Trustees of the Canadian Museum of Civilization in
Hull, Quebec. She is a noted writer of three books and used to work as
the Executive Producer and Host of a Canadian Broadcasting Corporation
(CBC) Television program. 
