<HEADLINE> Chinese President Urges Armed Police to Be Loyal (With More Details) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
wrote an inscription on July 16 for the Chinese People's Armed
Police's campaign of "trying to become a loyal guard of the Party
and the people."
</P>
<P>
The inscription reads: "Be a loyal guard of the Party and the
People forever."
</P>
<P>
Jiang is also general secretary of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee and chairman of the Central Military
Commission.
