<DOCNO> XIE19990909.0044 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 20:37 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egyptian Court Dismisses Suit Against British Paper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Cairo's Appeals Court on
Wednesday threw out a 16.5 billion U.S. dollars suit against a
British newspaper, which had published an article alleging
mistreatment of Christians in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The court approved an earlier ruling by South Cairo Court in
February, which dismissed the case, saying it did not have the
authority to rule it as it should have been filed in London where
the newspaper is produced.
</P>
<P>
The December case filed by an Egyptian lawyer, Mustapha Ashoub,
and 100 Coptic Christians against The Sunday Telegraph stemmed
from its report about a police crackdown on the Christians in the
southern town of al-Kosheh in August, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The plaintiffs demanded 10 billion British pounds (16.5 billion
dollars) from the newspaper as compensation for sullying Egypt's
reputation.
</P>
<P>
Ashoub, meanwhile, said he will resort to the Constitutional
Court, Egypt's highest court, to decide which court is entitled to
look into his case, court officials said.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper was also protected by other Egyptian laws that
prohibit courts from hearing cases filed by individuals who have
no direct interest in the outcome. Public interest petitions can
only be filed by the state prosecutor general.
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Telegraph article was written after police detained
hundreds of Coptic Christians in al-Kosheh during a murder
investigation. Human rights groups said many of the detainees were
beaten and tortured.
</P>
<P>
The allegations, denied by the Egyptian government, caused an
uproar in Egypt after international human rights groups and
Egyptian Copts abroad used it to support allegations that the
government discriminates against the Christian minority.
</P>
<P>
Coptic Christians make up about 10 percent of Egypt's 63
million people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990909.0045 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 20:37 </DATE_TIME>
