<HEADLINE> S. Africa Ranks 22nd Healthy Tourist Destination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- South Africa, out of a
total of 51 tourist destinations surveyed, ranks the 22nd place
according to the number of sicknesses reported.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics by the influential British Consumer's
Association show that about 16 percent of visitors to South Africa
reported one or more travel related illnesses when returning home.
</P>
<P>
This is against 5 percent in Belgium,18 percent in Australia,
20 percent in Zimbabwe, 27 percent in Kenya, 32 percent in the
Republic of Maldives, 40 percent in India, 58 percent in Mexico.
</P>
<P>
South Africa falls into the same risk group as the Caribbean,
Israel, Greece and New Zealand. It is by far the best rated
African country.
</P>
<P>
The three highest risk countries are Mexico, the Dominican
Republic and Egypt, while the three lowest risk ones are Britain,
Croatia and Belgium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
