<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100GMT, Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- Building contractor Veli Gocer, who built numerous
shoddy apartments in western Turkey, 90 percent of which collapsed
in last month's earthquake, is expected to be given a prison term
of between four and 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Local Daily News reported Wednesday that Gocer was arrested on
Monday in a friend's house in Alibeykoy in Istanbul, the largest
city of Turkey, and was then sent to the Bursa E-Type Prison in
western Turkey. (BC-Turkey-Quake-Contractor)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- The Cypriot government Wednesday firmly refused to
condition the start of peace talks on the recognition of the
breakway Turkish Cypriot republic in northern Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Government spokesman Michalis Papapetrou said that if Turkish
Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash and his supporter Turkey insist on
"the recognition of the illegal regime" in northern Cyprus as a
condition to start talks, no initiative on Cyprus will be able to
take place.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into Turkish Cypriots-controlled north
and Greek Cypriots-dominated south since 1974 when Turkish troops
invaded and occupied the northern third of the island in the wake
of a failed coup seeking union with Athens. (BC-Cyprus-Denktash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- A senior Kuwaiti official on Wednesday lashed
out at an Iraqi newspaper for its article on the latest
rapprochement efforts between Kuwait and Jordan.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi newspaper alleged that Kuwait urged Jordan, which
sided with Iraq in the 1991 Gulf War, to cooperate with it in the
efforts to isolate Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Jordanian King Abdullah Bin Hussein wound up a landmark two-day
official visit to Kuwait Monday, closing a decade-long
Jordanian-Kuwaiti estrangement. (BC-Kuwait-Iraq)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- An official of the Omani Defense Ministry
Wednesday denied media reports that Oman is planning to hold joint
navy maneuvers with Iran.
</P>
<P>
"What was carried by the media is totally untrue," the Oman
News Agency quoted the official as saying in Muscat on condition
of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, a spokesman for Oman's Royal Navy was quoted by
some reports as saying that preparations are under way for the
joint naval exercise that will take place "soon".
(BC-Oman-Denial-Exercise)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KHARTOUM -- Sudanese Foreign Minister Mustafa Othman Ismail has
expressed hope that the U.S. will receive positively the
Egyptian-Libyan initiative for resolving the Sudanese crisis.
</P>
<P>
Ismail made the remarks in the Libyan capital of Tripoli after
meeting with his Egyptian counterpart Amr Moussa and Libyan
Assistant Secretary of the General People's Committee on Foreign
Liaison for African Affairs Ali El-Turieki on the sidelines of the
ministerial meeting of the Organization of African Unity (OAU)
Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The recent Egyptian-Libyan initiative calls for a permanent
cease-fire and a national peace conference in an effort to end the
16-year-old civil war between the Sudanese government and the
south rebels. The war and the ensuing famine have claimed nearly 2
million lives in the poor African state. (BC-Sudan-US)

08/09/99 20:43 GMT

