<HEADLINE> Western European Union Intends to Cooperate With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Western European Union
(WEU), a growing defense organ of the European Union (EU), wishes
to carry out cooperation with China in safeguarding international
peace security, said a senior WEU official Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a written interview with Xinhua on the eve of her visit to
China, Lluis Maria de Puig, president of the Assembly of the WEU,
said that both the WEU and China want to see an improvement of the
security in their proper regions.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of the National People's Congress of China,
de Puig will start an official visit to China on September 9 and
will become the first WEU leader to visit China since 1985.
</P>
<P>
De Puig said that since the situation in one region of the
world can influence the security of others, it is extremely
important for different countries and international organizations
to meet and discuss the latest development of the world situation,
and the prevention and handling of crises.
</P>
<P>
The WEU leader pointed out that after the EU leaders decided to
reinforce their security and defense policy by integrating the WEU
into the EU during the Cologne Summit in June, the WEU's task has
become heavier and it needs a comprehensive picture of world
security.
</P>
<P>
"The WEU considers China as one of the most important actors on
the world stage because of its dimension, its human and natural
resources, its permanent membership at the United Nations Security
Council and the rapidness of its development," she said.
</P>
<P>
For this reason, the Paris-based organization will seek to
increase dialogue and cooperation with China, she said.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1955, the WEU now has 10 formal members, five
observatory countries and three associated countries in Western
Europe. It also has established relations of partnership with 10
Eastern and Central European countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
