<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Highlights of Today's Diplomatic News </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights
of the diplomatic news released by Xinhua here today.
</P>
<P>
Greek PM Postpones Visit to China
</P>
<P>
Greek Prime Minister Constantine Simitis has decided to
postpone his official visit to China originally scheduled between
September 15 and 21, due to the earthquake at home.
</P>
<P>
This was released by Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun
Yuxi here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Vice-Premier Meets OECD Secretary-General
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing met with Donald Johnson,
secretary-general of the Organization for Economic Cooperation and
Development (OECD), here today.
</P>
<P>
Li briefed the guest on China's economic situation and the
economic restructuring. He also expressed the hope that the OECD
would further its cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
Luo Gan Meets Vietnamese Visitors
</P>
<P>
Luo Gan, secretary of the Central Political Science and Law
Committee under the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China (CPC), today met with Phan The Hung, chief of the Internal
Affairs Commission of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
 Report on Religious Persecution in China Groundless: FM
Spokesman
</P>
<P>
The U.S. State Department report accusing China of persecution
of religious groups is groundless and wantonly interferes in China
's internal affairs, Foreign Ministry Spokesman Sun Yuxi said here
today at a routine press briefing.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that the report, submitted recently by the U.S. State
Department to U.S. Congress, is a gratuitous attack on China's
religious policy.
</P>
<P>
The Falun Gong group is not a religious organization, but an
anti-science, anti-humanity and anti-society group which actually
denigrates religions by falsely using the terms of Buddhism,
Taoism and Christianity to describe its philosophy, Sun said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Falun Gong cult poses a serious threat to
society and has been adamantly opposed by the people, particularly
religious personages.
</P>
<P>
To improve the implementation of the policy of freedom in
religion and to defend normal religious activities, the Chinese
government outlawed the cult, an act firmly approved by personages
in the religious circle and people with religious beliefs, Sun
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The overwhelming majority of the practitioners of the Falun
Gong cult have been freed from the cult group, and no question
whatsoever about them will be raised in this regard, Sun said,
adding that only very few members of the cult group who have
violated laws have been arrested and their trial will be conducted
according to legal procedures.
</P>
<P>
Sun said the allegations that over 40 Christians in Tanghe
County, Henan Province, were "persecuted", that the religious
freedom of the Catholics was restrained, and that some Catholic
dissidents were "persecuted", are sheer fabrications.
</P>
<P>
Sun reiterated that Chinese citizens' rights to religious
freedom and participation in normal religious activities are
protected by the Constitution and laws. Religious activities
should be carried out within the frame of law, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Those citizens who believe in religion and those who do not
enjoy equal rights and have the same obligations before law, with
no one enjoying special privileges, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Anyone who breaks the law and commits crime will be
investigated and held responsible for their law-breaking
activities in accordance with the law, regardless of whether he
believes in religion or not.
</P>
<P>
No body in China is detained or arrested because of religious
belief, Sun stressed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
