<HEADLINE> Jardine Insurance Brokers Penalized in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese insurance
authority today announced the imposition of a major penalty
against the British Jardine Insurance Brokers Limited for engaging
in unauthorized brokerage business in China.
</P>
<P>
A bulletin from the China Insurance Regulatory Commission (CIRC)
released here said the company's Beijing representative office
will be closed, and its chief representative in Beijing, Wang
Jiacong, will be disqualified from future service in the insurance
sector.
</P>
<P>
The CIRC launched a major campaign against illegal operators
and businesses in the insurance brokerage market in March this
year.
</P>
<P>
During this campaign, Jardine Insurance Brokers was found to be
engaging in unauthorized brokerage activities through its offices
in Hong Kong and on the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
The CIRC bulletin points out that Jardine Insurance Brokers
persisted with its illegal business even while the rectification
campaign was ongoing.
</P>
<P>
The company also attempted to hide its unlicensed business and
refused to admit that it had violated the Chinese insurance laws
and regulations, the CIRC said.
</P>
<P>
It added that the penalty is in accordance with the insurance
laws and is aimed at maintaining order in the insurance market and
protecting the interest of the insured.
</P>
<P>
The CIRC reiterated that overseas insurance organizations and
their representative offices in China shall not engage in any
insurance, reinsurance or brokerage business without its approval.
</P>
</TEXT>
