<DOCNO> XIE19990909.0073 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Computers Unaffected by "9999" Bug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The date September 9, 1999 may
have meant disaster for computers elsewhere in the world, as some
feared that computers could read the date code "9999" as a shut-
down order, but so far there have been no reports of such a
failure in China.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the special panel dealing with the Y2K
millennium bug in China confirmed this, and said the panel will
keep in touch with the country's key sectors for another two days
to stave off any possible computer failures.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has attached great importance to
addressing the "millennium bug," and has carried out several
thorough tests on computers nationwide. There is little chance of
computers being hit by bugs today, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Rising Technologies Co. Ltd., China's leading
software company, also reported no appeals for help today.
</P>
<P>
Han Xiaoqing, in charge of the technical department of Rising,
said that many of China's sectors were computerized later than in
Western countries and therefore almost all computers in China are
now Y2K-compliant.
</P>
<P>
The millennium bug, or the year 2000 (Y2K) problem, is a
holdover from the old method of coding the year as a two-digit
number in computer systems, which could cause computers to read
the year 2000 as the year 1900. There are also several other
dangerous days, including September 9, because of this old
practice.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Information Industry in China has long been
committed to the resolution of the millennium bug problem, and has
kept an close eye on key state enterprises which are the backbone
of China's national economy.
</P>
<P>
The number of computers in China is now surging at an annual
rate of 50 percent, and the country now has more than ten million
computers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990909.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
