<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Welcomes Foreign Cooperation to Build  Innovation System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- An official from the Ministry
of Science and Technology said China welcomes foreign cooperation
in building its national technological innovation system.
</P>
<P>
Sun Wanhu, deputy head of the International Cooperation
Department of the ministry, said here today at a ceremony for the
publication of the new book "50 Years of International Science and
Technology Cooperation" that his department is working to attract
high-level science-related ventures with Western countries.
</P>
<P>
Sun said his ministry will encourage Sino-foreign science and
technology cooperation and exchanges of major technological
innovation projects, especially those high-tech projects with good
market prospects.
</P>
<P>
He said China will strengthen cooperation and exchanges with
foreign countries on information, technology, personnel, funds,
and several other fields in an effort to speed up the development
of the country's high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
Hui Yongzheng, vice minister of Science and Technology, said at
the ceremony that China has so far established scientific and
technological cooperation ties with over 150 countries and regions
and signed 98 governmental science cooperation agreements with
dozens of foreign countries during the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
He said China has learned much from foreign countries in
scientific fields and improved its research and development
capacity accordingly.
</P>
<P>
Hui added that international science cooperation has also help
improve the quality of major projects and products, and encouraged
urban construction and the export of high-tech products.
</P>
<P>
The book was jointly compiled by the Ministry of Science and
Technology and the China Association for International Science and
Technology Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
It covers major policies of scientific development,
administrative systems, characteristics of foreign cooperation,
and major events and achievements in the course of Sino-foreign
cooperation.  
</P>
