<HEADLINE> ATMs in Beijing Recognize Local Bank Cards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- ATMs and POSs in Beijing are
now able to recognize 11 cards issued by eight local banks, thanks
to the ongoing Golden Card Project to popularize credit cards
nationwide, said Zhang Zhenming, general manager of the Beijing
Golden Card Networking Co., Ltd., at a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Anyone with any of the 11 cards can now draw cash at the ATMs
and make payments via the POSs at shopping centers.
</P>
<P>
Currently, there are over 800 ATMs and nearly 10,000 POSs
around the city, and 3.55 million cards are in use.
</P>
<P>
The eight banking institutions included in the network are the
Industrial and Commercial Bank, the Bank of China, the
Agricultural Bank of China, the Construction Bank, the Bank of
Communications, the Beijing Commercial Bank, the Post Bureau, and
the CITIC Bank.  
