<HEADLINE> ASEAN Social Security Organizations Meet in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- High-level delegates from Six
countries in Asia converged in Manila Thursday to ratify a
pan-Asia agreement on social security and discuss the challenges
of the next millennium.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Arellano, chairman of the Philippine Social Security
System (SSS), said the two-day meeting will approve amendments to
the membership and other administrative functions of the pan-Asia
organizations of the ASEAN Social Security Association (ASSA).
</P>
<P>
Arellano said the delegates will also discuss how to make ASSA
an effective and potent force and promote the cause of social
security in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The SSS head has been chosen to become the ASSA chairman during
a meeting of the ASSA in Singapore in July this year.
</P>
<P>
ASSA's Manila meeting is its fourth since the formal
establishment of the association in Bangkok in 1998.
</P>
<P>
ASSA members include social security organizations from
Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore, Thailand, Vietnam and the
Philippines. It aims to promote regional cooperation in all areas
of social security.
</P>
<P>
Arellano said that through the collaborative efforts of the
ASSA, social security organizations in the Asia-Pacific region are
prepared to meet the challenges of the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
"The challenges facing social security organizations around the
world are daunting," he said. "But by working together as a team,
we can look forward to the coming years with confidence." 
</P>
