<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian King Abdullah Bin
Hussein is expected to make an official visit to Lebanon next
Monday, the first by a Hashemite monarch to Lebanon in three
decades.
</P>
<P>
A statement from Lebanese President's office said the king is
visiting the country at the invitation of Lebanese President Emile
Lahoud, who had concluded an official visit to Jordan in May, the
first by a Lebanese head of state to Jordan in 25 years.
