since Syrian President Hafez Assad attended the late Jordanian
King Hussein's funeral in February and the new king made a visit
to Damascus in April.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon has been following the foreign policy of Syria, a main
power broker which is stationing 35,000 troops in the country.
</P>
<P>
Ties between Jordan, Syria and Lebanon cooled after King
Hussein signed a peace treaty with Israel in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Syria and Lebanon are technically still at war with Israel
which is in control of Syrian Golan Heights and south Lebanon.
</P>
