<HEADLINE> Turkish Forces Kill 15 Kurdish Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) have been killed in recent military
operations staged by the Turkish security forces in southeastern
Turkey, an official statement said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule, said the security forces had killed 14 PKK militants in
Mutki town of Bitlis province and one in Tunceli province.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, five PKK guerrillas were captured in Bitlis and
Hakkari provinces and two PKK militants surrendered to the
security forces also in the region, added the agency.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting since 1984 a war for an independent
Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey, which has claimed over
37,000 lives in the conflicts between the PKK and the security
forces. 
</P>
