<HEADLINE> China's First Multi-Function Credit Card Makes Debut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A credit card that can be used
for medical services and the receipt of indemnity from insurers
made its debut recently in north China's Tianjin Municipality.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC)
said today that the new credit card was issued by its Tianjin
Branch, with contributions from China Pacific Insurance Company
Ltd. and the Tianjin Municipal Department of Health.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the traditional cash, account, and credit uses,
the new card enables the holder to receive medical services at 25
hospitals in Tianjin as well as an under 10,000-yuan indemnity
from China Pacific in the event of accidental injury.
</P>
<P>
Applicants for the new card must pay an annual fee of 100 yuan
(12 U.S. dollars), according to the ICBC, and, on receiving the
insurance policy, cardholders are provided with the entire package
of services.
</P>
<P>
This new card will not only benefit customers by bringing them
more convenient services, but also broaden the vista for China's
financial and insurance market, analysts said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
