<HEADLINE> High Temperature Persists in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The temperature today in Wuhan,
capital of central China's Hubei Province, was 38 degrees Celsius,
the highest in a month.
</P>
<P>
The temperature on September 6 was 33.6 degrees C. and
yesterday it was 37.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Qisong, general engineer with the Wuhan Meteorological
Station, explained that the heat is due to the combined influence
of tropical high pressure over the Pacific Ocean and the Yangtze
River and the warm air mass over the Sichuan Basin.
</P>
<P>
The meteorological station predicts that the extreme heat will
persist in the city until September 11. 
</P>
</TEXT>
