<HEADLINE> Sino-American University of Silicon Lake Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The University of Silicon Lake,
a private institution of higher education in the city of Kunshan
in east China's Jiangsu Province, welcomed its first students
today.
</P>
<P>
The university has an investment of 500 million yuan, including
60 million U.S. dollars from Chinese American Dr. Steve Liang,
chairman of Morrison University in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The university has a capacity to educate 12,000 students, and
began today with a freshman class of 1,400 students selected
through the national college entrance examinations.
</P>
<P>
In conjunction with Morrison University, the new university's
diploma will be issued by the Ministry of Education and will be
recognized both in China and the United States.
</P>
<P>
University of Silicon Lake occupies an area of about 66.5
hectares, and is composed of eight schools including management,
the incorporation of machinery and electricity, environmental
science, electronics and information engineering, designing, law,
foreign languages, and biological engineering. The school will be
run by employing the management system of Morrison University.
</P>
<P>
The university has also set up a hi-tech garden nearby to
inspire the students and professors.  
