<HEADLINE> China's Mobile Telecom Sector Offers Business Opportunities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- China's huge potential mobile
telecommunication market has created a great number of business
opportunities for overseas investors, an industry official said
here today.
</P>
<P>
China has been working to upgrade its mobile telecommunication
industry by fostering innovation and using advanced technology
from overseas, said Ma Xiuhong, assistant minister of the Ministry
of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, at a forum on
international cooperation in mobile telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
This year, Ma said, China has adopted the policy of increasing
investment to stimulate economic growth, and investments in fixed
assets will rise by more than 20 percent, most of which will be
used for infrastructure including telecommunications and housing.
</P>
<P>
Ma said overseas investors are encouraged to engage in
manufacturing advanced telecommunication equipment and components
and parts in China through cooperative development, technology
transfer, and joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
Ma added that overseas-funded enterprises are also encouraged
to establish sales networks abroad and increase exports.
</P>
<P>
China's mobile-phone sales increased by some 10 million last
year, and experts say the growth rate will be maintained over the
next few years, and that by 2001 the country will have more than
90 million mobile-phone users.  
</P>
