<HEADLINE> China Finds Tuberculosis In Imported Boars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 9 (Xinhua)-- Officials of the animal and
plant quarantine bureau in Guangzhou, capital of south China's
Guangdong Province, have found tuberculosis in five boars
imported from Sweden.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time China has made such a discovery, said a
bureau official, who added that after a 45-day quarantine period
for 187 imported boars, five tested positive for tuberculosis.
</P>
