<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UPU Passes Beijing Postal Strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The 22nd Universal Postal
Congress (UPC) here today approved the Beijing Postal Strategy,
which will guide the development of postal services around the
world during the next five years.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Postal Strategy calls on the 189 member countries
of the Universal Postal Union (UPU) to focus on realizing
universal postal service, improve service quality of the
international postal network, enhance economic viability of this
network, explore postal markets and products, push forward postal
reform and development, and increase cooperation and interaction
among postal services.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from 11 UPU-member countries, including China,
Portugal, and Japan, made statements on the Beijing Postal
Strategy at the plenary meeting today.  
</P>
