<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A plot to assassinate
Philippine President Joseph Estrada and 19 other key government
and military officials has been uncovered, the official Philippine
News Agency (PNA) said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The PNA quoted a military report as saying that the terror plot
was to be implemented on the second half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The report said the assassination plot was contained in one of
the diskettes captured by the Armed Forces of the Philippines
recently.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the captured diskette points to a plan
called "special operations" to be carried out by rebels
nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The order to assassinate the president and 19 other
personalities was issued by the country's rebel National
Democratic Front on May 30 this year, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The planned "special operations" are part of a larger tactical
offensive to be carried out by the underground terrorists movement
in the second half of 1999, including raids, ambuscades and
attacks on military and civilian installations.
</P>
<P>
The president has been properly informed about the
assassination threat and the government has taken action on the
matter, said the report. 
