<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councilor on Improving Business Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councilor Wu Yi
has said that China will take further steps to improve its
business environment in a bid to draw more overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
These measures will include improving related laws and
regulations, making policies more transparent, cracking down on
corruption, and putting an end to all kinds of arbitrary charges,
fund-raising, fines and quotas, said Wu, also an alternate member
of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China (CPC), at a meeting Wednesday with about 60
business people from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that over the past two decades, China has made marked
progress in improving its business environment, especially its
infrastructure including transportation and power and
telecommunications facilities.
</P>
<P>
However, Wu said, there are still weak points in the "soft"
environment.
</P>
<P>
According to Wu, China has attracted total investments of more
than 280 billion U.S. dollars from overseas over the last 20 years,
some 60 percent of which came from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
</TEXT>
