<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Sharply Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks sharply
gained 498.25 points, or 3.73 percent, to close at 13,854.88
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the sharp rise of the Hong Kong stock market was
buoyed by a pact between Cable &AMP; Wireless Hong Kong Telecom with a
top U.S. group and by hopes of progress in China's World Trade
Organization membership bid.
</P>
<P>
Market turnover was 11.442 billion HK dollars (1.466 billion U.
S. dollars), 5.709 billion HK dollars (731 million U.S. dollars)
more than Wednesday's turnover of 5.733 billion HK dollars (735
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Sectoral sub-indexes for finance, utilities, properties and
commerce and industry made across-the-board increases of 1.85
percent, 6.65 percent, 3.14 percent and 4.04 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares ended with the Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index up 2.98 percent while the Hang Seng China-Affiliated
Corporations Index up 3.52 percent.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index dropped 33.34 points, or 0.25 percent,
to open at 13,323.29 on Thursday. The stocks sharply went up 353.
90 points, or 2.65 percent, to finish Thursday's morning session
at 13,710.53.  
</P>
