<HEADLINE> HKBAC to Launch Asia's Premier Business Support Facility </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Business Aviation
Center (HKBAC) will officially launch Asia's premier support
facility for business aviation on September 17, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Located at the Hong Kong International Airport, the center will
provide the smoothest and most rapid way to enter Hong Kong and
passengers can clear customs and immigration on site within two to
three minutes, a senior HKBAC official said at a press conference
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"They can also call on the wide range of information, transport
and concierge services, and it will operates as a base for private
and corporate owned aircraft in Hong Kong and the region," said
Paul Tsim, managing director of HKBAC.
</P>
<P>
Drawing on the strength of its major shareholders, China
Southern Airlines, the Kadoorie Group, Signature Flight Support
and Sun Hung Kai Properties Ltd., the venture will significantly
raise Hong Kong's profile as an international business city, the
director said.
</P>
<P>
Occupying a total floor space of nearly 100,000 square feet,
the center is fully equipped for aircraft fueling and other ground
handling operations.
</P>
<P>
Following the signing of a contract with Hong Kong's Airport
Authority in mid-1997 for a 15-year franchise, the center has
opened from a temporary terminal for the past year, Tsim said.
</P>
