<HEADLINE> China Builds Thermal Imaging Device Production Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Science and
Technology has decided to speed up the building of a production
base for thermal imaging devices, which can be widely used in
detection and maintenance of power systems, national defense,
smuggling detection, and fire prevention.
</P>
<P>
The ministry's high-tech industry department has listed thermal
imaging device production as one of the country's major high-tech
development projects.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou-based Sat Electric Infrared Technology
Corporation will be the country's first large-scales producer of
the devices and is expected to become operational next year.
</P>
<P>
An official with the ministry said the production base will
have an annual capacity to turn out over 2,000 infrared
televisions, 500 thermo-vision devices, and another 100 units of
motor-vehicle-based thermal imaging devices by the end of next
year.
</P>
<P>
The devices detect infrared radiation from the surface of
materials and than reflect the images of the materials.
</P>
<P>
The devices can spot potential weaknesses in power systems,
find and rescue people in trapped in fires, and can also be used
for fire prevention on military ships and in armories.  
</P>
</TEXT>
