<HEADLINE> Sensex Falls on Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive Index (SENSEX)
dropped 17.03 points Thursday on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE)
following heavy purchases from Foreign Institutional Investors and
domestic financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share sensitive index opened better at 4,783.40 but
later moved in an extremely narrow range of 4,795.59 and 4,745.00
before closing at 4,764.59 as against Wednesday's close of
4,781.62, showing a net fall of 17.03 points.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index dropped moderately by 8.28 points to 2,138.21
from the previous close of 2,146.49.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 index and the Dollex were quoted fractionally down
at 497.03 and 190.19 compared with previous close of 497.17 and
190.24 respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 index was almost steady at 1,471.90 as against
Wednesday's close of 1,472.20. 
</P>
