<HEADLINE> Macao-Moscow Flight to Be Opened in Mid-October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Domodedovo Airlines of
Russia will start weekly flights between Moscow and Macao
beginning from October 15 this year, according to a press release
issued Thursday by the Macao International Company.
</P>
<P>
A four-engine Ilyushin Il-96-300 wide-body aircraft, flight 725,
will leave Moscow's Domodedovo Airport every Friday at 4:30 p.m. (
Moscow time) and fly non-stop to the Macao International Airport
at 6:20 a.m. (Macao time) on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The return flight of 726 will leave Macao at midnight on
Saturdays and arrive in Moscow at 6:20 (Moscow time) on Sunday
mornings.
</P>
<P>
Manufactured by Russia's Ilyushin Aviation Complex, the
aircraft has 22 seats of Business Class and 230 seats of Economy
Class. Similar planes have been used by Russian airlines on inter-
continental routes since 1993.  
</P>
