<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's 1st Under-15 Soccer Championship to Kick Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia will hold its
first nation-wide under-15 youth soccer championship in capital
Addis Ababa next week, the Ethiopian Football Federation announced
here.
</P>
<P>
The tournament, scheduled to kick off at Addis Ababa Stadium on
September 14, is expected to feature youth teams from all of the
country's 11 federal states.
</P>
<P>
The competition is specially organized for those involved in
the nation-wide youth soccer training project launched a couple of
years ago, the federation said.
</P>
<P>
It also noted that all participating teams should strictly
observe the age limit regulation or face stern measures for any
violation of that type.
</P>
<P>
Reportedly, in the past two annual soccer competitions for the
under-17 youth, the age problem was evident.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian Football Federation said that extra caution will
be taken in order to penalize those clubs who come up with players
over the age of 15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
