<HEADLINE> Karachi Stocks Rally on Good News </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Karachi stocks rallied
Thursday amid strong buying from local and foreign funds on the
news that some headway has been made on the Independent Power
Producers (IPPs) issue.
</P>
<P>
The 100-share price index of the Karachi Stock Exchange closed
11.32 points, or 0.98 percent higher to 1,161.19 from Thursday's
1,149.87.
</P>
<P>
The trading volume on Thursday stood at 141.383 million shares
against Wednesday's 128.993 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Strong buying emerged in the power sector on the news that the
Economic Coordination Committee has okayed agreements between the
government and six IPPs, which is indicative of the possibility of
the final resolution of the power tariff dispute, said a dealer.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 166 active issues, gainers beat losers 66 to 54
while 46 remained unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
