<HEADLINE> APEC Must Continue to Focus on Economic Cooperation: Chinese FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AUCKLAND, New Zealand, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Asia-Pacific
Economic Cooperation (APEC) must continue to focus on economic
cooperation and should not discuss political, security and social
and other sensitive or controversial issues, Chinese Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the 11th APEC Ministerial Meeting, the Chinese
foreign minister noted that over the past decade since its birth,
APEC has vigorously carried out cooperation on the basis of the
voluntary will of its members and achieved marked progress.
</P>
<P>
"Ten years' development has already turned APEC into a forum
for its members to conduct consultations on an equal footing and
mutually beneficial cooperation for greater confidence among them.
It has played a positive role in promoting regional and global
economic development," he said.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing and summarizing the development path of APEC and
further clarifying its development directions, the Chinese foreign
minister noted that first and foremost, APEC must continue to
focus on economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"APEC is a forum for economic cooperation created in response
to the development needs of the Asia-Pacific region and
development trends of global economy. Its purpose is to 'reduce
economic disparities among members and achieve common prosperity.'
The past 10 years' experience is a proof that one of the most
fundamental causes for the steady development and progress
achieved by APEC is the commitment of all the members to the
fundamental objective of economic cooperation by proceeding from
their common economic interests.
</P>
<P>
"At present the changing situation has required us to readjust
priorities within the framework of economic cooperation," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese foreign minister said China supports any new
element in the content of cooperation as long as it directly bears
on economic development and helps deepen the APEC community
spirit, promote cooperation and facilitate the common development
of all the member economies.
</P>
<P>
"That's why we are not in favor of APEC discussion of
political, security and social and other sensitive or
controversial issues, for such discussion will only result in
differences and adversely affect cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"This does not serve the common interests of APEC members, nor
does it conform to the original intention for the establishment of
APEC," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Secondly, Tang said, APEC shall stick to its cooperation
approach suited to this region. "After 10 years of exploration,
APEC has formed an APEC approach that recognizes diversity,
stresses flexibility and adheres to consensus, voluntarism and
gradual progress," he added.
</P>
<P>
The APEC approach provides the only feasible cooperation model
for this region and it is also of great immediate importance for
forging worldwide fair, equitable and reasonable new international
economic ties, he said.
</P>
<P>
Thirdly, Tang added, APEC shall continue to focus on
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"Paralleled development of trade and investment liberalization
and economic and technological cooperation is an important
innovation of APEC and also a major feature that distinguishes
APEC from other organizations of economic cooperation," he said.
</P>
<P>
While calling for more attention to developing economies, he
said that with the ever closer interdependence among the
economies, "development of only a few countries won't lead to a
sustained and stable growth of world economy as a whole."
</P>
<P>
"To ensure a balanced development of APEC, it is utterly
important to reverse the situation in which APEC's economic and
technological cooperation lags behind trade and investment
liberalization," tang stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
