<HEADLINE> China's Ice City Preparing to Welcome New Millennium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said at a press conference that China has themed next year's
tourism campaign "New Millennium China 2000."
</P>
<P>
On Dec. 31, the ten cities will lead a series of gala events to
welcome the 21st century, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
Harbin Mayor Cao Guangliang said that his city will spend 33
million yuan to build a snow and ice wonderland which will cover
280,000 sq meters -- ten times larger than the famous Zhaolin Ice
Lantern Park in the city.
</P>
<P>
The site will require 70,000 cubic meters of ice and 130,000
cubic meters of snow. Some 10,000 ice and snow sculptures will be
on display.
</P>
<P>
The area will be divided into four parts: Jubilee Square,
Sounds of the Century, Adventure Paradise and Cartoon World.
</P>
<P>
During the eight-week festival, various cultural and commercial
activities will be held, including the naming of 200 Snow Whites
and Millennium Ice Beauties, Cao said.
</P>
<P>
Harbin's annual snow and ice festival has become one of the
largest events of its kind in the world.  
</P>
