<HEADLINE> Hangzhou Spends Six Billion Yuan on Road Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Construction began recently
on an expressway encircling Hangzhou, capital of east China's
Zhejiang Province, the largest highway project ever carried out in
the renowned tourist destination.
</P>
<P>
The 112.4-km expressway will cost more than six billion yuan (
about 723 million U.S. dollars) and is scheduled to be open to
traffic in 2002 and will link some national highways.
</P>
<P>
Traffic congestion in Hangzhou is expected to be dramatically
improved as a result of the new road, which also will further
promote the growth of the highway network in the province.
</P>
