<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Checks Arbitrary Charges For Overseas-Funded Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Municipal People's
Government has started a strict check on illegal and arbitrary
charges levied against overseas-funded enterprises in this major
port city in north China.
</P>
<P>
The review, jointly carried out by the Tianjin Administration
of Commodity Prices and Tianjin Foreign Economic and Trade
Commission, is meant to reduce the financial burden on the
overseas-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Fee charged since 1998 on all relevant administrative bodies,
institutions and agencies are subject to the check.
</P>
<P>
Illegal actions include unauthorized fees, arbitrarily raised
fees, failure to implement government preferential policies, and
fees charged for free services.
</P>
<P>
According to government officials, enterprises will be
compensated for all confirmed illegal and arbitrary charges, and
those responsible will be punished.
</P>
<P>
More than 12,000 overseas-funded enterprises now are located in
Tianjin with a total investment of 10.7 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
