<HEADLINE> Homing Pigeons Released to Mark Macao's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A total of 1,999 homing pigeons
were released Thursday morning at a famous downtown scenic spot in
Macao, unveiling a series of activities marking the 100-day
countdown to Macao's return to China.
</P>
<P>
The pigeons came from more than 400 raisers in Guangzhou,
capital city of Guangdong province. It takes about one hour for
the homing pigeons to fly back to their owners some 100 km away.
</P>
<P>
"The pigeons flying freely in the sky indicate that Macao is
returning to the embrace of the motherland," said Liu Chak Wan,
vice-director of the Macao Basic Law Promotion Association which
is the organizer of the pigeon releasing.
</P>
<P>
"They also take away our strong aspiration for Macao's smooth
return and the best wishes for a peaceful world," Liu said.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 2,000 children cheered and waved colorful
balloons on the occasion. And a large crowd of residents and
tourists was attracted to view the spectacular scene. 
</P>
</TEXT>
