<HEADLINE> Hunting Areas In Northern China To Be Open To All </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- China's Shanxi Province is
planning to build 5 large hunting areas, with central government
approval, where people who get a game license from the local
forest authority can hunt deer, wild boar, pheasant, and rabbits.
</P>
<P>
Work on the first of the 5, the International Oriental Hunting
Field, a 27,000-hectare area in the Taiyue Mountain forest
district near Qinyuan county, is underway. The villas and service
area have been completed and the whole project is expected to be
completed in three years. It will be the first international
hunting area opening to the public in this area.
</P>
<P>
Total acreage of the five sites is about 112,000 hectares. Each
area will hire professional field managers, keepers, and guides.
Construction work on the other 4 areas is under way. Local
officials have chosen the locations, amount of acreage, and animal
species, and roads are being built.
</P>
<P>
The 4 areas will primarily be open to Chinese and will be open
to foreign visitors at a later date.  
</P>
