<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National Unity Helping Economy In Northwestern Autonomous Region (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 9 (Xinhua) -- New relations among the ethnic
groups of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region have
developed over the past 50 years, according to Abul'ahat Abdurixit,
chairman of the regional people's government.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic groups are involved in mutual development and shared
prosperity with help from successful Communist Party policies, he
told Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang has 47 ethnic groups, 13 of which have lived in the
region for generations. Since the peaceful liberation of Xinjiang
in 1949, ethnic minorities have rid themselves of the oppression
of reactionary rulers and enjoy equality. In 1953, the first batch
of townships governed by ethnic groups were set up and five ethnic
minority prefectures and counties were established the following
year. The Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region was founded on October
1, 1955 by the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
The region opened a new chapter in Xinjiang's developmental
history and the past five decades have been the fastest period of
development, Abul'ahat Abdurixit says.
</P>
<P>
The number of cadres from ethnic groups has grown from some 3,
000 in the early 1950s to 320,000. The autonomous region's Ninth
People's Congress has 542 deputies, 357 of whom are from ethnic
minorities.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990909.0253 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National Unity Helping Economy in Northwestern Autonomous Region (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The autonomous regional government places great stress on
national unity and uses education about nationhood and patriotism
to maintain regional stability, equality and unity, Abul'ahat
Abdurixit says. Every May a national unity education day is
designated.
</P>
<P>
At present, the various ethnic groups in Xinjiang have mutual
trust, respect, and support, and learn from each other. The idea
that one can not live without the help of others has taken root
here, he adds.
</P>
<P>
The people of the autonomous region love the Communist Party
and socialism, safeguard national unity, oppose divisiveness, and
cooperate fully to contribute to social stability and the
prosperity of all ethnic groups, he says.
</P>
<P>
This unity has paved the way to economic growth and the region
has an economic system with agriculture as the foundation and
industry as a mighty pillar. It is now the largest cotton producer
and a leading petrochemical center in the country.
</P>
<P>
With support and assistance from the central government, there
have been a great number of key infrastructure projects in
Xinjiang to provide a solid base for 21st century development.
</P>
</TEXT>
