<HEADLINE> Nepal, Bhutan to Hold Talks on September 13 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The 8th Nepal-Bhutan Joint
Ministerial Level Committee (JMLC) meeting over the Bhutanese
refugee crisis will begin here on September 13, The Kathmandu Post
quoted the Foreign Ministry as saying Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is expected to discuss the repatriation of 100,000
Bhutanese refugees living in eastern Nepal after they fled Bhutan
around the 1990s.
</P>
<P>
The 7th JMLC meeting held in Kathmandu in 1996 ended in impasse
as Nepal insisted on the repatriation of all refugees, while
Bhutan wanted to take back only those who were forced to flee the
country.
</P>
<P>
Nepal has been seeking cooperation from India in resolving the
refugee crisis, as India handles Bhutan's foreign affairs.
</P>
<P>
According to officials from the Foreign Ministry, the Bhutanese
refugee issue is also on the agenda of the Indian Foreign Minister
Jaswant Singh's present visit to Nepal on September 8-11. 
