<HEADLINE> Jiang Praises Sino-Australian Economic, Trade Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The close trade and economic
ties between China and Australia make a firm foundation for
bilateral relations and have brought enormous benefits to the two
countries as well as the livelihood of the two peoples, visiting
Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Today, China and Australia have become each other's important
trade and investment partners," Jiang said Thursday morning during
a meeting with members of the Australia-China Business Council and
representatives of corporations.
</P>
<P>
"Our two economies are highly complementary to each other.
Australia is economically developed and rich in natural resources.
It has an edge in many areas such as energy, transportation,
telecommunications, mining, environmental protection, finance and
insurance," he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed, "All these industries and infrastructure have been
identified by China as its priority areas for development in the
coming years."
</P>
<P>
Therefore, Jiang said, there is a great potential for bilateral
cooperation. He hoped the council would continue to play its
unique role and promote and assist the mutually beneficial
cooperation between the business communities of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that people from the Australian economic and trade
community come and visit China and work together with their
Chinese counterparts to create a better future for Sino-Australian
economic cooperation and trade," he said.
</P>
<P>
One of the important objectives of his current visit is to
deepen the mutually beneficial cooperation between the two
countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the past few days, he continued, economic cooperation and
trade have always been an important topic both in his talks with
Prime Minister John Howard and in his meetings with local leaders
of Australia.
</P>
<P>
"We have shared the view that our bilateral trade and economic
relations have entered a period of sound development and there is
a vast vista for expanding and deepening these ties between us,"
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that he is convinced that so long as the business
communities of the two countries spare no effort in enhancing
cooperation and exploring new fields for cooperation, bilateral
economic cooperation and trade will develop to a new high.
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation and trade constitute an important
component of the Sino-Australian relationship, Jiang said, adding
he is glad to see the satisfactory development in the bilateral
economic ties and trade in the past 27 years owing to the joint
efforts by the business communities.
</P>
<P>
The volume of bilateral trade increased from 87 million U.S.
dollars at the establishment of diplomatic ties to a record high
of 5.3 billion in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The two-way investment has kept a momentum of continuous
increase and it has expanded its coverage to include almost all
trades, such as
finance, insurance, metallurgy, construction materials, textile,
electronics, machinery, petroleum, light industry, chemical
industry and tourism.
</P>
<P>
Describing the Australia-China Business Council as an important
organization, Jiang praised its "great deal of useful work" for
the enhancement of cooperation and exchanges in the bilateral
economic ties and trade, and its role as an important bridge
linking the two sides.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Jiang is expected to attend a luncheon
hosted jointly by Howard and premiers and chief ministers of
Australia.
</P>
<P>
Jiang will proceed to Cairns Friday before ending the state
visit in Australia on September 11. 
</P>
</TEXT>
