<HEADLINE> Taoist Mountain in Northeast China Under Restoration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A massive five-year
restoration project has started on a Taoist mountain in northeast
China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Tiecha Mountain, situated at the Manchu Autonomous County of
Benxi City, is the birthplace of Taoism in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
It stretches over 10 kilometers, with its highest peak at an
elevation of 912.9 meters, and has dozens of ancient temples.
</P>
<P>
The whole mountain area is designated as China's national
forest park and attracts millions of sightseers and pilgrims every
year.
</P>
<P>
The mountain has been restored many times before, but the
current work is the most extensive in its history, with an
estimated cost of over 10 million yuan. 
</P>
