<HEADLINE> New Terminal of Beijing's Capital Airport to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The new terminal of the
Capital International Airport in Beijing has passed an initial
quality inspection and will be put into trial operational on
September 20.
</P>
<P>
The test run will last one year before a final examination for
the formal operation of the new facility, an airport official said
today.
</P>
<P>
The new terminal, four times larger than the current facility,
covers 336,000 square meters and is equipped with state-of-the-art
facilities. It has four stories, including one underground. The
main entryway is about 120 meters long and 28 meters high.
</P>
<P>
The present premises of the Capital Airport, which was built in
1955, cannot handle the rising passenger and cargo volume, and
aviation authorities started the airport expansion project in
October 1995.
</P>
<P>
With the new terminal in full operation, the airport will be
able to handle 35 million passengers and 190,000 flights a year,
the official said.  
</P>
