<HEADLINE> Chinese Universities Help Poor Freshmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Universities in China are
working on a variety of programs to help poor freshmen begin their
studies. The measures adopted include scholarships, loans,
allowances, reduction or exemption from tuition and work
opportunities, today's "China Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing based English newspaper quoted an official from
Qinghua University as saying that no student will be forced to
quit college because of poverty.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the university set up a "green passage" from Beijing
railway station to the students' dormitory.
</P>
<P>
Students from poor families or regions were able to get loan
notices which they could hand in directly to the registration
office for part of all of their tuition fees.
</P>
<P>
The policy has been extended this year to cover more items for
which students must pay.
</P>
<P>
The tuition fee for most universities in Beijing is around 3,
000 yuan (360 U.S.dollars) per year. Undergraduate students also
need to pay 500 yuan to 1,000 yuan (60 U.S.dollars - 120 U.S.
dollars) per year for accommodation.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University has allowed new students from poor families
to defer payment of their tuition fees. Some poor first-year
students can obtain temporary subsidies. Those among the top five
of their provinces in the national college entrance examinations
are entitled to a new student scholarship worth 4,000 yuan (480 U.
S.dollars).
</P>
<P>
Similar programs or policies are being carried out in other
major universities, the paper says.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Education is also helping poor students.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, interest-free loans have been offered to poor
college students, and special scholarships have been granted to
students who major in agriculture, teaching and some other special
fields, and students from ethic minorities.
</P>
<P>
The ministry requires that at least 10 percent of tuition fees
collected by colleges should be spent on helping poor students,
the paper reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
