<HEADLINE> Hungary Hopes for Role in Regional Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Hungary hopes to play an
active role in the implementation of the Stability Pact for
Southeastern Europe (SPSE), introduced by the European Union, said
to a Economic Ministry press release.
</P>
<P>
Hungary also wants Italy's support on this matter, said the
ministry in the press release issued Wednesday after talks between
Hungarian Secretary of the Economic Ministry Gabor Gulacsi and
visiting Italian Secretary for Foreign Affairs Umberto Ranieri.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Gulacsi said the situation in southeastern
Europe has direct influence on Hungary, and the country is also
interested in economic stability and development in this region.
</P>
<P>
The government of Hungary plans to provide loans to
entrepreneurs in Yugoslavia to buy Hungarian machines. This way,
Hungarian enterprises could participate in economic reconstruction
in southeastern Europe, Gulacsi said.
</P>
<P>
Hungary, whose economy has suffered great losses in the past
ten years because of the situation in Yugoslavia, hopes the
Italian government will support it, the secretary added.
</P>
<P>
The SPSE, which was adopted in Cologne, Germany, on June 10,
1999, during an international meeting on the Balkan issue, is
aimed at sustaining long-term stability and security in the Balkan
region through measures such as promoting market economic
development and establishing regional security coordination.
</P>
