<HEADLINE> Rafter Forced out of Davis Cup Due to Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Pat Rafter has been forced
out of this month's Davis Cup match between Australia and Russia
because of the shoulder injury that sidelined his U.S. Open tennis
defense.
</P>
<P>
"Pat saw the doctor yesterday. He feels that Pat should take at
least six to eight weeks off," Davis Cup captain John Newcombe
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Wayne Arthurs, Mark Woodforde, Andrew Ilie and Jason
Stoltenberg will fight for the other singles berth during a week
of trials before the September 24-26 match in Brisbane. 
