<HEADLINE> EDS-Updates with more details (UPDATE) Japan's Economy Up in 2nd Quarter of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Japan's gross domestic product (
GDP) rose 0.2 percent in the second quarter of 1999, the Economic
Planning Agency said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It marked the second quarter in a row of growth after 2.0
percent in the period from January through March.
</P>
<P>
The growth was a surprise as economists surveyed by Dow Jones
Newswires had predicted Japan's GDP would contract 0.3 percent in
the second quarter from the first.
</P>
<P>
The planning agency attributed the economic growth largely to
public works spending and housing investment in the April-June
period.
</P>
<P>
Japanese Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi, who took office in July
last year, has vowed to recover Japan's economy and raise the
annual growth rate to at least 0.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese government also announced earlier this week that
increasing demand from Asian countries was behind recent growth in
Japan's industrial output. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
