<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern Rail Line Construction Underway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Workers are lay tracks on a 143-
km-long railway from Kanshi, in southeast China's Fujian Province,
to Meizhou, in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The line will be built at a total cost of 2.62 billion yuan (
315.66 million U.S. dollars) and is scheduled to be open to
traffic in August 2000.
</P>
<P>
This will be an important transport passage to further
invigorate the economy of eastern and southern parts of the
country, a Ministry of Railways official noted.
</P>
<P>
The journey from Fuzhou, the provincial capital of Fujian, to
Guangzhou, the capital city of Guangdong, will be shortened by 515
km when the line is completed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
