<DOCNO> XIE19990909.0298 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang-Clinton Meeting to Be of Great Significance: Chinese FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AUCKLAND, New Zealand, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The forthcoming
meeting between the Chinese and United States presidents will be
of great significance to the improvement of Sino-U.S. relations,
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after a meeting over breakfast with U.S.
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright, Tang said that more
significantly, the summit meeting will have important and
far-reaching influence on the development of trans-century
Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and his U.S. counterpart Bill
Clinton will meet on the sidelines of the 7th informal meeting of
leaders of the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) forum
scheduled for September 12-13 in Auckland.
</P>
<P>
Describing his meeting with Albright as "candid, useful and
significant," Tang recalled that the exchange of visit between
Chinese and U.S. heads of state and Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji's
visit to the United States in March served as a momentum and
opportunity for the development and improvement of the relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
But a series of ensuing developments, particularly the May 7
U.S. bombing of the Chinese Embassy in Yugoslavia, "have worsened
Sino-U.S. relations, and the responsibility is entirely on the
U.S. side," he said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, whether Sino-U.S. relations can continue to be
improved depends on whether the U.S. side can create favorable
conditions for the improvement of the relations by taking concrete
actions and steps, Tang stressed.
</P>
<P>
Tang said another point he stressed to Albright was that "the
question of Taiwan is still the most sensitive, most salient and
most important issue in Sino-U.S. relations."
</P>
<P>
"It is imperative that the United States should have a clear
recognition of the serious nature of this question and the
possible harm it could bring to Sino-U.S. relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that Lee Teng-hui is the biggest troublemaker, the
biggest obstacle and the biggest stumbling block in the way of
development of Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has repeatedly reiterated its adherence to the
one-China policy, its "three-no" commitment and its abiding by the
three Sino-U.S. joint communiques, and Secretary Albright made a
clear-cut statement on these points in today's meeting, the
Chinese Foreign Minister said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
