<DOCNO> XIE19990909.0300 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> McEnroe Named U.S. Davis Cup Captain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- John McEnroe's long-time
dream of serving as captain of the United States Davis Cup team
became a reality Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
United States Tennis Association president Judy Levering
announced McEnroe's appointment Wednesday at the National Tennis
Center in New York.
</P>
<P>
"It's one of the proudest moments of my life," McEnroe said. "
The time is right for me now."
</P>
<P>
McEnroe, one of the greatest players of all-time who won 77
singles and 77 doubles titles, becomes the 37th U.S. Davis Cup
captain, replacing Tom Gullikson, the captain since 1994.
</P>
<P>
Levering said the selection process began at the beginning of
last month, when she met with Pete Sampras, Andre Agassi, Jim
Courier and Todd Martin to get their input on what they look for
in a captain.Each player submitted a list of two or three people
they would play for in Davis Cup.
</P>
<P>
"They all said they want to play for John McEnroe," Levering
said.
</P>
<P>
McEnroe joined the U.S. Davis Cup team at the agoe of 19 in
1978, he compiled a 59-10 record in 30 ties over 12 years and
played on Cup-winning teams in 1978, 1979, 1981, 1982 and 1992. He
holds American Davis Cup records for wins, ties played, years
played and singles wins.
</P>
<P>
"John personifies the spirit and tradition of Davis Cup,"
Levering said. "We are extremely pleased that he has decided to
accept the captaincy and are confident that he will be able to
convery his passion for Davis Cup to all the players on the team."
</P>
<P>
McEnroe expressed that his first priority as captain would be
to convince Sampras and Agassi to play. Agassi sat out a loss to
Australia in the quarterfinals this year while Sampras played only
doubles.
</P>
<P>
"I hope I garner enough respect to get Andre and Pete to play,"
McEnroe said. "Who doesn't want to see them play Davis Cup?"
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, Agassi said he would never play Davis Cup
again, but there's reason to believe he will change his stance
with McEnroe as captain.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, on the other hand, has said he only would play for
Gullikson, whose twin brother, Tim, was Sampras' coach until dying
of brain cancer in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Sampras did not play Davis Cup in 1998 or in this year's first-
round match against Britain. He returned to the team for the
quarterfinals against Australia, but Gullikson honored the
commitments of Martin and Courier.
</P>
<P>
McEnroe, who expressed his interest in playing Davis Cup
doubles as recently as a few months ago, stated that it is "
certainly doubtful" that he would take the court.
</P>
<P>
With doubles as the weak point of the U.S. team in recent years,
McEnroe responded that "having Sampras and Agassi winning three
out of four singles matches" would alleviate the need for a solid
doubles team.
</P>
<P>
Gullikson finished with a 13-5 record in six years at the helm
of the team. During his tenure, the American squad defeated Russia
for the 1995 title and lost to Sweden in the 1997 finals.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Gullikson's efforts had been plagued by an
inability to get steady commitments from Sampras and Agassi. With
a weakened squad, the Americans fell to Italy in the 1998
semifinals and to Australia in this year's quarterfinals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
