<HEADLINE>   Tyson to Fight Orlin Norris on October 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Mike Tyson has chosen Orlin
Norris as his first opponent since his release from a jail, and
the fighting date is scheduled on October 23, at the MGM Grand in
Las Vegas.
</P>
<P>
The 12-round fight is being billed as something called the WBC
international heavyweight title, according to the Associated Press
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The long-awaited fight will be televised on Showtime. Norris is
the 33-year-old brother Terry Norris, who used to be one of the
best super middleweight fighters in the world.
</P>
<P>
Tyson, who had served 3 1/2 months in a Maryland jail for
assaulting two motorists over a fender-bender, first chose the 33-
year-old former undisputed heavyweight champion James Douglas as
his opponent, but Douglas was ruled out for poor physical
condition.
</P>
<P>
Tyson, who left the jail on May 24, is already training in Las
Vegas. The former heavyweight champion knocked out Francois Botha
in the fifth round on January 16 in the MGM Grand. It will be only
the second time in his 10 fights since 1990 that Tyson has not
fought on pay-per-view.
</P>
<P>
Norris was a WBA cruiserweight champion in 1993-95. He has a
record of 50-5 since 1986 with 27 knockouts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
