killed and 50 injured as ruling Taliban bombed a busy bazaar in
the northern Afghan town of Taloqan, the country's opposition
forces said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Taliban aircraft continued to carry out sorties over Taloqan
today. This morning, one of Taloqan's busiest bazaars came under
direct enemy fire," opposition commander Sayed Anwari said in an
