China is open-minded on the suggestion and it would like to
make a further study of the suggestion, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese envoy emphasized that the consent and cooperation
from the Indonesian government is very important before the
Council makes any decision on the matter.
</P>
<P>
"Otherwise I don't think the peace-peeking mission will be
successful," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that any peace-keeping activity must be
authorized by the Council. 
